data.name: betaLabel.Text
data.value:
This is a BETA version of WinAuth {0}. PLEASE MAKE A BACKUP COPY OF YOUR CURRENT AUTHENTICATOR FILES.
You will find the authenticator file in your application folder:
Windows 7/Vista/2008 - "c:\Users\<username>\AppData\Windows Authenticator\" XP/2003 - "c:\Documents and Settings\<username>\Application Data\Windows Authenticator\"
Unless you have saved your authenticator under a different name, it may be called authenticator.xml.
Once you have copied these files, you will be able to restore a previous version of WinAuth. If you are at all unsure, click Cancel or remove the authenticator from your Battle.net account before proceeding.
